' @id(USE-VIEW-DIAGRAMS)
' @desc(USE-VIEW-DIAGRAMS, "Developer views a rendered model diagram on the in-app canvas with shapes and text legible.")
' @id(USE-FISHEYE-FOCUS)
' @desc(USE-FISHEYE-FOCUS, "Developer focuses on part of a diagram via a center-fixed fisheye that magnifies the canvas centre and compresses content toward the edges, layered on the scroll global zoom.")
' @id(USE-TOGGLE-PANELS)
' @desc(USE-TOGGLE-PANELS, "Developer collapses or expands the left MODELS panel and the right MODEL CONTEXT panel via an inner-edge handle, reclaiming canvas width on demand.")
' @id(USE-VIEW-OCL)
' @desc(USE-VIEW-OCL, "Developer selects an .ocl constraint file and views it on the canvas with a Source/Diagram toggle: Source shows the raw OCL text, Diagram shows a synthesized PlantUML constraints diagram.")
' @id(USE-VIEW-DEPLOY)
' @desc(USE-VIEW-DEPLOY, "Developer sees /mdd-deploy deployment diagrams (.mdd/deploy/**/*.puml) in `mdd view`, listed in a DEDICATED 'DEPLOY' rail section that is visibly labelled as a utility artifact OUTSIDE the current<->objective parity gate. Selecting one paints its already-rendered .mdd/rendered/deploy/**/*.svg on the same canvas. The section is a THIRD viewer ingestion source alongside the model registry and the cycle registry; deployment files never enter ModelRegistry, so /mdd-validate and /mdd-review still never read .mdd/deploy/.")
' @id(USE-VIEWER-THEMED)
' @desc(USE-VIEWER-THEMED, "Developer sees the mdd-viewer chrome dressed by a Catppuccin palette (Mocha when the OS is dark, Latte when light, picked once per frame from the OS appearance), bundled Inter for UI text and JetBrains Mono for code/diff lists, and softened item spacing + corner rounding — instead of the bare egui defaults. Cross-platform single binary; chrome only — the SVG canvas rasterizer is untouched.")
' @id(USE-VIEW-PUML-SOURCE)
' @desc(USE-VIEW-PUML-SOURCE, "Developer reads the raw PlantUML text of the selected model file via a Source toggle placed next to the Diagram (and Diff) toggle in the central panel. Source replaces the rendered diagram with read-only, scrollable .puml text (@id/@ref/@desc/@sec markers and @startuml/@enduml directives highlighted); toggling back to Diagram repaints the SVG. Mirrors the OCL Source/Diagram functionality but for ordinary model diagrams — no new rendering, the source is read straight from disk.")
' @id(USE-OPEN-RENDER)
' @desc(USE-OPEN-RENDER, "Developer, with a mockup .puml selected whose slug has a React render, clicks an 'Open render' button on the central-panel view-tab row; the viewer starts the mockups Vite dev server (port 4317) if it is not already running and opens the OS browser at /mockup/<slug>. The button is disabled when the selection has no render.")
' Objective-side use-case view. Same text-legibility acceptance as before,
' plus the focus+context fisheye, the collapsible side panels, an
' OCL constraint viewer, a dedicated non-gated DEPLOY section, an
' OS-appearance-following Catppuccin theme with bundled fonts, and a
' Source toggle that shows a model file's raw PlantUML beside its diagram.
' The toolbar no longer carries zoom controls.
title mdd view — diagram viewer (objective)

left to right direction

actor "Developer" as Dev <<missing>>

rectangle "mdd-viewer" {
  usecase "View rendered diagram\n(shapes AND text legible)" as View
  usecase "Browse model files" as Browse
  usecase "Pan and zoom canvas\n(scroll zoom, drag pan)" as PanZoom
  usecase "Focus via center fisheye" as Fisheye
  usecase "Collapse / expand side panels" as Panels
  usecase "Inspect model IDs and trace links" as Trace
  usecase "View OCL constraints\n(source or diagram)" as ViewOcl
  usecase "View deployment diagrams\n(dedicated DEPLOY section,\nNOT parity-gated)" as ViewDeploy
  usecase "View themed viewer chrome\n(Catppuccin, bundled fonts,\nOS appearance auto-follow)" as Themed
  usecase "View PlantUML source\n(Source toggle next to Diagram)" as ViewSource
  usecase "Open React mockup render\n(button opens browser)" as OpenRender
}

Dev --> View
Dev --> Browse
Dev --> PanZoom
Dev --> Fisheye
Dev --> Panels
Dev --> Trace
Dev --> ViewOcl
Dev --> ViewDeploy
Dev --> Themed
Dev --> ViewSource
Dev --> OpenRender

View ..> Browse : <<include>>
View ..> PanZoom : <<extend>>
View ..> Fisheye : <<extend>>
View ..> Panels : <<extend>>
View ..> Themed : <<include>>
View ..> ViewSource : <<extend>>
ViewOcl ..> PanZoom : <<extend>>
ViewDeploy ..> PanZoom : <<extend>>
OpenRender ..> Browse : <<include>>

note bottom of OpenRender
  Objective (USE-OPEN-RENDER): the central-panel view-tab row
  shows an "Open render" button (UIC-OPEN-RENDER in
  MCK-VIEWER-FULL). It is enabled only when the selected file
  is a mockup whose slug has a React render
  (mockups/src/mockups/<slug>.tsx). Click starts the Vite dev
  server in mockups/ if :4317 is not already serving, then opens
  the OS browser at /mockup/<slug>. Realized by SEQ-OPEN-RENDER;
  launcher owned by CMP-MOCKUP-LAUNCH.
end note

note bottom of ViewOcl
  Objective (USE-VIEW-OCL): selecting a
  .mdd/constraints/*.ocl file shows a
  Source | Diagram toggle on the canvas.
  Source = raw OCL text (read-only,
  @id/context/inv highlighted); Diagram =
  a synthesized PlantUML constraints diagram
  (context box + inv notes + @ref to the
  DOM- it constrains) rasterized through the
  existing SVG pipeline. Realized by
  SEQ-VIEW-OCL.
end note

note bottom of View
  Objective: every label, actor, message and
  note in a rendered diagram is visible in the
  in-app canvas. Realized by SEQ-RENDER-DIAGRAM-PAGE
  which must consult a populated font database
  (DOM-FONT-DATABASE) before rasterizing.
end note

note bottom of Fisheye
  Objective (USE-FISHEYE-FOCUS): the canvas applies a
  center-fixed fisheye over the rendered diagram — the
  centre bulges/magnifies and content compresses smoothly
  toward the edges. Layered ON TOP of the existing
  scroll-to-zoom global zoom; drag still pans to bring a
  region into the magnified centre. Realized by
  SEQ-CANVAS-FISHEYE.
end note

note bottom of PanZoom
  The toolbar no longer has Reset / Zoom + / Zoom -
  buttons. Zoom is scroll-only (global, at cursor);
  the fisheye is the focus mechanism on top of it.
end note

note bottom of Panels
  Objective (USE-TOGGLE-PANELS): each side panel shows
  an inner-edge chevron handle; clicking it collapses
  the panel to a thin sliver, clicking the sliver
  re-expands it. Realized by SEQ-PANEL-COLLAPSE.
end note

note bottom of Themed
  Objective (USE-VIEWER-THEMED): on startup
  MddViewer registers a bundled Inter (UI) and
  JetBrains Mono (monospace) FontDefinitions
  set, then on every frame asks dark-light for
  the OS appearance and applies catppuccin_egui
  Mocha (dark) or Latte (light) plus tightened
  spacing.item_spacing and softened widget
  rounding. No new SVG rendering, no new model
  state — chrome only. Realized by SEQ-APPLY-THEME
  and owned by CMP-VIEWER-THEME.
end note

note bottom of ViewDeploy
  Objective (USE-VIEW-DEPLOY): the left rail gains a
  THIRD source. Today MddViewer::new() loads exactly
  two — model_registry() (.mdd/models + .mdd/constraints)
  and cycle_registry() (.mdd/cycles); .mdd/deploy is
  reachable only as RenderTree::Deploy (an `mdd render`
  rasterization target), so it never appears in the
  interactive viewer. Objective: a dedicated DEPLOY
  section, fed by Project::deploy_files(), lists
  .mdd/deploy/**/*.puml and paints the existing
  .mdd/rendered/deploy/**/*.svg on the shared canvas.
  It stays OUT of ModelRegistry: /mdd-deploy is a
  utility outside the parity gate, so /mdd-validate
  and /mdd-review must continue to ignore .mdd/deploy/.
  Realized by SEQ-VIEW-DEPLOY.
end note

note bottom of ViewSource
  Objective (USE-VIEW-PUML-SOURCE): the central panel
  toggle row gains a "Source" button between "Diagram"
  and "Diff". Selecting it puts the viewer in
  View::Source, which paints the selected model file's
  raw .puml text — read-only, scrollable, with @id /
  @ref / @desc / @sec markers and @startuml/@enduml
  directives highlighted — instead of the rendered SVG.
  No new rendering: the text is read straight from disk
  (analogous to the OCL Source sub-mode, which never
  depends on a rendered artifact — OCL-PUML-SOURCE-NO-RENDER).
  Toggling back to "Diagram" repaints the SVG canvas.
  Realized by SEQ-VIEW-PUML-SOURCE; state held in
  DOM-PUML-SOURCE-VIEW.
end note
@enduml
